theorem closure_interior_iterate_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) {n : ℕ}
    (hn : 0 < n) :
    (Function.iterate (fun S : Set X => closure (interior S)) n) A = closure (interior A) := by
  -- Set up the operator `T := closure ∘ interior`.
  let T : Set X → Set X := fun S => closure (interior S)
  -- We will prove the desired equality by induction on `n`.
  -- The base case `n = 1` is immediate by unfolding `Function.iterate`.
  -- For the inductive step we use the idempotency of `T`, namely
  -- `closure (interior (closure (interior S))) = closure (interior S)`.
  -- This is given by `Topology.closure_interior_idempotent`.
  cases n with
  | zero =>
      exact (Nat.lt_asymm hn hn).elim
  | succ n =>
      induction n with
      | zero =>
          simp [T, Function.iterate]  -- `n = 1`
      | succ n ih =>
          -- Use the inductive hypothesis together with `iterate_succ_apply'`.
          have : (Function.iterate T (n.succ.succ)) A =
              T (Function.iterate T (n.succ)) A := by
            simpa [Function.iterate_succ_apply'] using rfl
          -- Rewrite using the inductive hypothesis and idempotency of `T`.
          simpa [T, ih, Topology.closure_interior_idempotent] using this

theorem interior_inter_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ interior A ∩ interior B := by
  intro x hx
  have hxA : x ∈ interior A :=
    (interior_mono (Set.inter_subset_left : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A)) hx
  have hxB : x ∈ interior B :=
    (interior_mono (Set.inter_subset_right : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ B)) hx
  exact ⟨hxA, hxB⟩
